    <text>
        <body>
            <pb facs="" xml:id="leaf001r" type="recto"/>
            <div1 type="poem">
               
                <head type="main-authorial">BECAUSE I SPOKE OUT</head>
            
            
                <lg type="stanza">
                
                    <l>The last hired mourner went off </l>
                    <l>to look for comfort among fools. </l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                    <l>(I could stand naked in this huge town square </l>
                    <l>lit up by the phosphorescences of the stillness</l>
                    <l>and there would be no intruders to stare at me. </l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                    <l>Oh this desertion is deadly</l>
                    <l>it makes its own chill sprout from the flames.) </l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                    <l>I hope someone will come to hear me again</l>
                    <l> and weep with me to the end.</l>
                    </lg>
                    <lg>
                    <l>Maybe then I'll be strong enough to make the truth less bitter.</l>
                </lg>
              <note type="editorial" target="#hsm"> [HSM] </note>
            </div1>
        </body>
